          "message": "feat(gnovm): make stringŌåÆslice conversion capacity deterministic (#5182)\n\ncloses: #5183\n**Summary**\nGoŌĆÖs `append` growth strategy is intentionally unspecified and can\nchange between Go versions, which makes slice capacity (`cap`)\nnonŌĆædeterministic. In Gno, `string`ŌåÆ`[]byte` and `string`ŌåÆ`[]rune`\nconversions were inheriting that runtime behavior, so the resulting\ncapacities could differ across versions even with identical inputs. This\nPR forces `cap == len` for both conversions, making capacity\ndeterministic and stable across Go versions, and adds a file test that\nlocks in the expected behavior for both byte and rune conversions.\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Morgan Bazalgette <morgan@morganbaz.com>",
          "timestamp": "2026-02-23T18:48:37+01:00",
