          "distinct": true,
          "id": "72c432b695917740563fef0a881c7b960e19b4ee",
          "message": "fix(gnovm/doc): use import path instead of package name in package line (#5262)\n\n`newPkgDataFromMemPkg` was setting `importPath` to `mpkg.Name` (the\npackage name, e.g. \"ed25519\") instead of `mpkg.Path` (the full import\npath, e.g. \"crypto/ed25519\"). This caused `gno doc` to emit a wrong `//\nimport \"...\"` line for packages whose name differs from their path.\n\nUpdate the existing `TestJSONDocumentation` expected value (which was\naccepting the wrong output) and add a `TestDocument/importPath`\nregression test.",
          "timestamp": "2026-03-23T14:23:33+01:00",
          "tree_id": "5b099a5d59e58b6bff50865b0dfb0539e2d60700",
          "url": "https://github.com/gnolang/gno/commit/72c432b695917740563fef0a881c7b960e19b4ee"
