          "distinct": true,
          "id": "b9778503678046f152c37b9b52226981e3efdbf3",
          "message": "fix(gnoland): prevent duplicate validator removals in EndBlocker (#5356)\n\n## Summary\n\nFixes the test11 chain halt at block 702499, where the node crashed with\n`\"failed to find validator to remove\"` after proposals 13 and 14 were\nexecuted in consecutive blocks.\n\n**Root cause**: `fireEvents()` in `execution.go` fires `EventTx` AFTER\nblock commit. The validator event collector picks these up, so block N's\nevents trigger block N+1's EndBlocker. `GetChanges(from)` used an\nunbounded inclusive range on the AVL tree, causing the same removals to\nbe returned twice across consecutive EndBlocker calls.\n\n**Fix**: Change `GetChanges(from)` to `GetChanges(from, to)` with a\nbounded `[from, to]` range. The EndBlocker calls `GetChanges(h, h)`\nwhere `h = LastBlockHeight()`, fetching exactly one block's changes per\ncall.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `TestGetChanges_BoundedRange` ŌĆö Gno realm test verifying bounded\nrange semantics on the real AVL tree\n- [x] `TestEndBlocker/consecutive_proposals_cause_duplicate_removal` ŌĆö\nUnit test reproducing the exact test11 scenario\n- [x] `TestReproduceTest11ChainHalt` ŌĆö Integration test with real node:\ncrashes without fix (`signal: terminated`), survives with fix\n\n## Breaking change\n\n`GetChanges` signature changed from `GetChanges(from int64)` to\n`GetChanges(from, to int64)`. The only caller is the EndBlocker in\n`app.go`.\n\n­¤ż¢ Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.ai/claude-code)",
          "timestamp": "2026-04-09T12:42:33+02:00",
